topic.title: Auto Provision
topic.shortdesc: Release notes for Auto Provision on Yeastar S-Series VoIP PBX.

li.p: Added support for Gigaset N670 IP PRO and N870 IP PRO.
Added support for Tiptel phones: 3310, 3320, 3330, and 3340.
Fixed Fanvil X7 issue: Auto provisioning for Side Keys didn't take effect.
Fixed Fanvil X210 issue: Auto provision for the 92th Function Key didn't take effect.
Fixed the Custom Template issue: The Fanvil X1, X1S, and X1SG options were not available when configuring the custom template.
Fixed Grandstream （2135, 2170）issue: Auto provision for Account Label didn't take effect.

section.title: Version 1.8.19
section.p:
Released Date: February 27, 2020
Fixed the issue of Yeastar TA Gateway: The option list of IAX Audio Codes displayed incorrectly.
Optimized Cisco SPA Phones: Added support for a maximum of 255 characters in Dictionary Server Script field.In the earlier version, the maximum length allowed is 63.

section.title: Version 1.8.16
section.p:
Released Date: December 12, 2019
Fixed the Custom Template issue: The contents in Others tab were missing.
Optimized the mechanism of applying configuration changes to improve the system stability.
You don't need to click Apply button to reload Asterisk if you save unchanged configurations.
If no Apply button appears after you save some specific configuration changes, then the configurations can be saved without reloading Asterisk.

ul.li: Added support for Yealink phones: SIP-T41U, SIP-T43U, SIP-T46U, and SIP-T48U.
Added support for Htek phones: UC902S, UC921, UC921G, UC503, and UC503G.
For Fanvil X4 phones: Added BLF/DTMF and BLF/Conference subtype options for Memory DSS key.
For Snom phones (D1XX series, D3XX series, and D7XX series): Added the Administrator Mode, Administrator Password, HTTP Server Username, and HTTP Server Password settings in the Preference tab.

section.title: Version 1.8.13
section.p:
Released Date: October 22, 2019
Added support for the following IP phones:
Fanvil: X210, X210i, X1, X1S, X1SG, X2C, X3SG, X3U, X4U, X5U, X6U, X7, X7A and X7C
Snom: D385, D735 and D717
Yealink: VP59 and W60B
Polycom: VVX411
Optimized DSS settings of Fanvil phones (X5/X5G,X4/X4G,X5S and X6): Added Action URL type of DSS key.
Optimized Custom Template of Snom phones:You can add custom parameters in the custom template.
Fixed the issue of Snom phones: The phones did not reboot automatically after performing auto provision.
Optimized settings of Snom phones (D305, D315, D345 and D375): Added the Tone Scheme setting in Preference tab.
Optimized the IP address of Snom phones: Whatever the Web Server Type you set for the phone, you can click the IP address that is displayed on the Device List page to access the IP phone.
Optimized the issue of Snom phones: Even through you didn't upload the phone firmware to the PBX, an error of firmware upgrade failed would be displayed on the IP phone.
Fixed the auto provision template issue of Fanvil phones: The value of <language> parameter in the template was incorrect.
Fixed the issue of Custom Template: Custom template did not take effect if you added devices in bulk or imported an auto provisioning file.
Fixed the issue on Firmware Upgrade page: The uploaded firmware wasn't be displayed on Firmware Upgrade page after upgrading the phone version.

ul.li: Optimized DSSKey/Line Key setting: The Value field is allowed to enter maximum 255 characters.

li.p: Optimized Account settings for IP phones: The extension Caller ID Name will be automatically filled in the Label field.

p.note: In the earlier version, the extension number will be automatically filled in the Label field.

ul.li: Fixed the issue of Backup and Restore: The backup file didn't contain Auto Provisioning Custom Templates,which led to an error on custom template after restoring data from the backup file.
Changed the model name of Yealink SIP-W60B from SIP-W60B to W60B(W60P/W53P/W41P/CP930W-Base).
Fixed the phonebook issue on Yealink W60B: Only 5 handsets could download the phonebook from PBX after auto provisioning.
Fixed the issue of Auto Provision Template: The special characters %cn in the custom template could not be identified correctly and would be deleted.
Fixed the issue of Auto Provisioning Device List page: The Auto Provisioning Device List could not display if the assigned extension name contained a line break.

li.p: Fixed the DSSkey issue on Fanvil: The DSSkey setting could not take effect when the DSSkey Line is set to Auto.
Fixed the issue on Fanvil: Fanvil phones could not download phone book files after auto provisioning,
Fixed the issue of Auto Provision Template: The setting in Other tab would be cleared if the characters ` was contained in the custom template.
Fixed the issue that the auto provisioning would be failed after restoring configurations from a backup file.

ul.li: Fixed the issue on Yeastar TA FXS Gateway: If you disabled an FXS port, the port settings could not be cleared after auto provisioning.
Fixed the issue on Cisco: The Cisco DTMF could not work after auto provisioning.
Fixed the issue of Grandstream GXV3240 and GXV3275: The Russia Time Zone was incorrect.
Fixed the issue of Custom Template: When adding devices in bulk, the selected custom template could not take effect after auto provision.
Added support for Yealink phones: SIP-T53, SIP-T53W, SIP-T54W, and SIP-T57W.

li.p: Added support for configuring VPK (Virtual Multi-Purpose Keys) on Grandstream GXP2170.

ul.li: Optimized Extension Board Key Settings of Grandstream GXP2170: Up to 40 EXT keys can be configured.
Fixed the phonebook issue on Snom phone: Some contacts are missing after provisioning.
Optimized Auto Provisioning template: Blank spaces are allowed in the Name filed.

Optimized the compatibility of Auto Provisioning and Hot Standby: To ensure that IP phones remain registered, the auto provisioning configurations are updated automatically according to the Hot Standby configurations.
Optimized DSS Key Settings of Fanvil X6: Special character & is allowed in the URL Value field.
Optimized Auto Provisioning template: A template error would error if the special character & was contained in the customized parameters.
Fixed the Yealink Auto Provisioning: The phone web page could not be accessed if the special character ! was contained in the Admin Password.
Fixed Auto Provisioning issue: Auto provision Yeastar TA1600 V3, TA2400 V3, or TA3200 V3 could not work properly.
Added support for Yealink T40G.
Added support for Vtech ET635 and ET605.
Added support for importing an CSV file to assign extensions to multiple phones in bulk.
Increased the number of phone Line for Htek UC9XX.
Increased the number of phone Line for Yealink W60B.
Added support for configuring iLBC_13_33kbps and iLBC_15_2kbps on Yealink phones.
Added Short Name setting for Cisco phones.
Added Name option on Line Key Settings page for Fanvil C400 and C600.

The default setting of Web Server Type is changed to HTTPS ONLY for the following Snom phones:
D120、D712、715、725、D745、D765、D785、D305、D315、D345、D375
Optimized Custom Template for Yealink and Vtech phones: Added support for adding parameters in custom template.
Fixed the issue that if a Yeastar TA FXS gateway was auto provisioned by the PBX, the TA FXS ports could not receive incoming calls.
Fixed the issue that adding contacts on Auto Provisioning web page would cause excessive CPU consumption.
Fixed the issue that the Line key settings for Fanvil X6 were incorrectly auto provisioned.
Fixed the issue on Yealink T46S and T46G: Failed to upgrade the phone firmware by Auto Provisioning.
Fixed the issue that Auto Provisioning Phonebook could not work properly.
Added support for the Vtech phones: ET685, VDP650, VCS752.
Optimized the web interface page.

Added support for the following phones:
Snom D712, D725, D745, D765, D785, D120, M215 SC, C520-WiMi
Htek UC926E, UC924E, UC912, UC912G, UC802T, UC803T, UC804T, UC804G, UC806T, UC806G
Gigaset Maxwell basic, Maxwell 2, Maxwell 3
Optimized the Time Zone setting of Yealink, Snom, Htek, and Gigaset phones.
Fixed the issue that Grandstream phones would reboot continually if the PBX was in Hot-Standby status.
Fixed the time zone settings issue on Fanvil phones.
Compatible with Yeastar S-Series VoIP PBX v30.7.0.10.

Added support for the following IP phones:
Snom D715
Escene ES330-PEG, ES330-PEN, ES620-PEG, ES280-P, ES206-PN, ES205-PN
Univois U6S, U1S, U3S
Added support for auto provisioning transfer mode on Yealink phones.
Added support for dynamic VPK keys on Grandstream phones.
Added Name setting for Fanvil X4 DSS Key.
Added support for Fanvil X3S template.
Added the date format DD/MM/YYYY for Yealink T41S.
Added “Default” language setting for Yealink phones.
Updated default templates for Snom phones.
Fixed the issue that if a phone was provisioned with multiple accounts, only one account name was displayed.
Fixed the issue that PBX could not scan and detect Yealink T40G.
Fixed the issue that PBX could not scan and detect Tiptel phones.
Fixed the issue that auto provisioning for Snom phones only worked when the “Register Name” was the same as the extension number.
Fixed the DSS key issue on Fanvil X6.
Fixed the voicemail issue on Yealink default template.
Fixed the translation error on German web.

Added support for the following IP phones:
Yealink CP860, CP960, CP920, W60B
Fanvil H2, H3, H5
Mitel 6863i, 6865i, 6867i, 6869i, 6873i

Optimized Daylight Saving Time setting:
If you set Daylight Saving Time to Automatic, you can set a location for your time zone.
Changed the default language of Fanvil phones to English.
Added support for auto provisioning BLF keys on Vtech VSP735.
Added support for auto provisioning the settings on Cisco SPA phones: admin password, time zone, daylight saving time, language, dictionary server script.
Fixed the issue that auto provisioning for DSS keys on Fanvil phones could not work.
Fixed the issue that auto provisioning of Yealink T23P could not work.
Fixed the issue that auto provisioning of Fanvil X5S could not work.
Fixed the provisioning issue on extensions: the register name of extension is incorrect.
Added support for the compatibility with S-Series firmware 30.5.0.30 version.
Added support for Yealink IP Phones: T52S, T54S.
Added support for Yealink IP Phones: T58A, T58V, T56A.
Added support for Fanvil IP Phones: X2, X6.
Fixed the Cisco SPA IP Phone auto provisioning issue: provisioning file created failed.
Fixed the Yealink IP Phone auto provisioning issue: not able to choose Location when Daylight Saving Time is Automatic.
Fixed the issue that auto provision for Grandstream GXP 3240 could not work.
Fixed the Yeastar TA Gateway auto provisioning issue: when scanning the devices in the LAN, the TA devices would not be updated.
Fixed the issue that auto provision for Snom IP Phones function key and Label could not work.
Fixed the Tiptel 32XX series IP Phone auto provisioning issue: IP Phones could not download the provisioning files.
Fixed the Time Zone saving failed issue.
Fixed the PnP server memory leak issue.
Fixed Auto Provisioning issue: after upgrading the Auto Provisioning App, the Grandstream phone configurations would disappear.
Added support for Akuvox IP phones: SP-R50P, SP-R52P, SP-R53P, SP-R55P, SP-R59P, SP-R55G, SP-R59G, SP-R63G, SP-R67G, VP-R47P, VP-R47G, VP-R48G, and VP-R49P.
Added support for Alcatel IP phones: IP251G, IP301G, IP701G, and IP2115.
Added support for Fanvil IP phones: X4 and X5S.
Added support for Yealink IP phones: T41S, T42S, T46S, T48S and T27G.
Added support for Panasonic IP phones: HDV100, HDV130, HDV230, HDV330 and HDV430.
Added support for auto provisioning Dutch language for Yealink phones.
Fixed TA provisioning issue: setting “Key as Send” to “Disable” could not take effect.
Fixed Yealink provisioning issue: if the extensions were registered by auto provisioning method, users could not successfully call back from the phone’s history.
Added support for French, Italian Web interface.
Updated Turkish Web interface.
Added Auto Provisioning Template feature. Users could add a template first, then apply the template settings to specific IP phones or gateways.
Fixed auto provisioning issue: the system would respond NOTIFY packages to all local the IP phones, and caused registration failure for the non-auto-provisioned IP phones.
Added support for Alcatel IP phones: IP100, IP150, IP151, IP300, IP700G, IP1850 and IP2015.
Added support for vTech IP phones: VSP600A, VSP610A, VSP715A, VSP716A, VSP725A, VSP726A, VSP735A, VSP736A and VCS754A.
Added support for provision Yealink phone to Czech web language.
Added support for Fanvil MAC address fields: 00a859, 00b869, 0c385E and 0c386E.
Added “Hostname” setting for Yeastar TA gateways.
Fixed the issue that auto provision for Tiptel 30XX series phonebook could not work.
Fixed the issue that auto provision for Grandstream GXP 2160 could not work.

Fixed the Yeastar TA gateway auto provisioning issue: if the TA gateway’s LAN settings were not edited, the TA gateway’s IP address, hostname, web login username and password would be cleared; some specific TA ports might not be registered.
When you upload Tiptel phonebook to S-Series PBX, you can choose phone type and upload different phonebooks.

Added support for the following IP phones:
Cisco SPA301, SPA303, SPA501G, SPA502G, SPA504G, SPA508G, SPA509G, SPA512G, SPA514G, SPA525G2, CP7821
Polycom VVX101, VVX201, VVX300, VVX310, VVX400, VVX500, VVX600, VVX601, VVX1500, IP321, IP331, IP335, IP450, IP550, IP560, IP670
Htek UC902, UC903, UC923

Auto Provisioning supports the following IP phones:
Yealink T19P-E2, T21P-E2, T23G, T23P, T27G, T29G, T40P, T41P, T42G, T46G, T48G, T49G, W52P, W56P
Fanvil C01, C400, C58/C58P, C600, X3/X3P/X3SP, X5/X5G
Snom 320, 710, 715, 720, 725, 760, 765, D305, D315, D345, D375
Grandstream GXP1100, GXP1105, GXP1160, GXP1165, GXP1400, GXP1405, GXP1450, GXP1610, GXP1620, GXP1625, GXP1628, GXP1630, GXP2130, GXP2135, GXP2140, GXP2160, GXP2170, GXP2200, GXV3240, GXV3275
Htek UC802, UC803, UC804, UC806, UC840, UC842, UC860, UC862, UC924, UC926
Tiptel 3110, 3120, 3130, 3210, 3220, 3230, 3240, 3245, 3275, 3220XL
Fixed the issue that if you reset the system, Auto Provisioning could not work properly with TFTP server.
